description:
Thanks to everyone for your encouraging support! =)
Sorry, I have never been good with note blocks. ; )

World Seed: -5414202391146285944
World Download: http://www.mediafire.com/?fv81lti4fmeqfnn

When I was planning this video I decided I wanted something amazing in the foreground, and something amazing in the background.

The TNT Beats is what I chose to do for the foreground. Originally I planned on having much much more TNT... including cannons. However, I began experiencing severe lag issues and other problems early on. Surrounding the TNT partially with obsidian helped to reduce lag from the block drops, but it became clear I had to stop using TNT for the second half of the video. You can see towards the end of the mine cart ride things were getting very choppy already and the map wasn't loading.

The Etho'fied Nether is what I did for the background... something to appease people if their eyes wandered from the TNT. I always felt that the Nether has amazing level generation which is under appreciated due to the dull lighting and block textures, and lack of block variety. A few simple steps in mcedit transformed the dull terrain into one of the most beautiful areas I have ever seen in Minecraft.

Song: "Temperence", by Matt McFarland
Website: http://www.mattmcfarland.com/
Thanks for providing people with excellent music that we can use.
